<section sectnbr = "1D">
<servcat sctnbr = "01" scnbr = "04">
<configtype typenbr = "3">
<servinfotype sitcode = "4">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "S8T40A1434003" svcinfotypenbr = "06" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Valve Clearance Inspection and Adjustment
</title>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
For identification of each cylinder, refer to 
<intxref refid = "S8T40A1120009">Precautions for Identification of Cylinder:J24B</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<servinfosub id = "S8T40A1434003001">
<title>
Inspection
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect negative (&#8211;) cable from battery.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove cylinder head cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "S8T40A1436010"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove engine under cover.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Align timing mark (3) on exhaust camshaft timing sprocket with match mark (2) on camshaft housing No.1, by turning crankshaft pulley (1) clockwise with 19 mm wrench.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I8T401142005.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "64.914mm" ver = "02" gw = "165" gh = "167"/>
</figure>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I8T401142006.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "51.156mm" ver = "02" gw = "192" gh = "128"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Measure valve clearances with thickness gauge according to the following procedures.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Measure valve clearances of indicated valves &#8220;A&#8221; in figure.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Turn crankshaft pulley 360&#176; clockwise with 19 mm wrench.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Measure valve clearances of indicated valves &#8220;B&#8221; in figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I8T401142007.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "57.858mm" ver = "01" gw = "202" gh = "147"/>
</figure>
</s2>
</s1>
<ptxt>
If valve clearance is out of specification, record valve clearance and adjust it to specification. 
</ptxt>
<spec-sdm>
<sdm-title>
Valve clearance specification
</sdm-title>
<sdm1>
<sdm-condition>
When cold (ECT: 15 &#8211; 25 &#176;C (59 &#8211; 77 &#176;F))
</sdm-condition>
<sdm2>
<sdm-condition>
Intake
</sdm-condition>
<sdm-value>
0.16 &#8211; 0.24 mm (0.0063 &#8211; 0.0094 in.)
</sdm-value>
</sdm2>
<sdm2>
<sdm-condition>
Exhaust
</sdm-condition>
<sdm-value>
0.31 &#8211; 0.39 mm (0.0123 &#8211; 0.0153 in.)
</sdm-value>
</sdm2>
</sdm1>
</spec-sdm>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "S8T40A1434003002">
<title>
Adjustment
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove tappet to be replaced. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "S8T40A1436021"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Select proper size of tappet as follows.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Using a micrometer, measure the thickness of the removed tappet (1).
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Calculate the thickness of new tappet by formula below.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
If the number at second places of decimal point A is odd number, use (A &#8211; 0.01) tappet.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<ptxt>
Intake side:
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
A &#x003D; B &#x002B; C &#8211; 0.20 mm (0.0079 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Exhaust side:
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
A &#x003D; B &#x002B; C &#8211; 0.35 mm (0.0138 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
A: Thickness &#8220;a&#8221; of new tappet
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
B: Thickness &#8220;a&#8221; of removed tappet
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
C: Measured valve clearance
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A141015.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "65.267mm" ver = "01" gw = "174" gh = "168"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Select new tappet closest to calculated value from available size as a spare part.
</ptxt>
</s2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install tappets and camshafts. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "S8T40A1436021"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Recheck valve clearance.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
